This paper deals with mechanism design and auction theory, which are core topics in computer science and economics. The paper specifically focuses on revenue optimization for selling a single item to agents with independent but non-identically distributed values, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and computational economics (cs.EC). The paper also uses mathematical optimization techniques and regularity properties, which are common in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms and bounds, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
